ings will be of interest to scholars in philosophy, film, literature, and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aclaire denis, jean luc godard, proust, pierre bergounioux, connectedness, community, dependence, intimacy, society, psychoanalysis, oneness, unity, universality, descartes, cosmology, freud, genet, illegitimacy, being, nothingness, senses, external world, knowing, philosophy, nonfiction, thoughts, mind, ontology, meaning, purpose.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106904390 cprintz978022620605940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226206196423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226206196/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles